<task id="011" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-02 New `sprk_analysisplaybook` configuration "Summarize Document for Chat"</title>
    <status>complete</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort>~1 hour (definition-authoring portion only; combined with task 010 into one JSON file; main session handles the Dataverse deploy + commit)</actual-effort>
    <assigned>AI Agent</assigned>
    <started>2026-06-04</started>
    <completed>2026-06-04</completed>
    <phase>Phase 2 — Vertical Slice + Insights Tool Integration</phase>
    <wave>P2-G1 (parallel-safe with 010; co-deploys with the action seed; both gate P2-G2 via 012)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Phase 1 ✅ (all P1 tasks complete); co-deploys with 010 (action seed must be upserted before the playbook resolves its `actionCode` FK)</dependencies>
    <tags>dataverse, playbook, config, data-deploy</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Ship the new `sprk_analysisplaybook` row "Summarize Document for Chat" as a JPS-style
    playbook definition JSON committed to the repo and deployed to Spaarke Dev via the
    existing `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` script. The playbook wires the new
    `sprk_analysisaction` seed authored in task 010 (D2-01) into a single-node
    `AiAnalysis` playbook whose shape mirrors the existing in-repo Insights playbook
    JSON convention (`*.playbook.json`) — specifically the structure documented in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json`
    and `universal-ingest.playbook.json`. The downstream `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`
    (D2-03, task 012) resolves THIS playbook to drive the chat-driven Summarize
    vertical slice; the `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` (D2-05, task 015) and the
    `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` endpoint (D2-04, task 014) both converge
    on the same playbook row.

    **Reuse mandate, hard** (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1): the playbook record MUST mirror the
    existing in-repo `*.playbook.json` schema (top-level `playbook` block + `nodes` array +
    `dependsOnGraph` + `acceptanceCriteria`). It MUST NOT invent new schema fields, new
    Dataverse entities, or a new playbook envelope. The Summarize playbook
    (GUID `4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988`) is the existing wizard-path playbook
    and is referenced for parity by `design.md` §2 / `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`
    §3.2; this new "Summarize Document for Chat" playbook is its chat-pane sibling
    (different action seed, different orchestrator entry, same output schema family —
    `ISummarizeResult` / `DocumentAnalysisResult` per spec FR-01 acceptance).

    **No new Dataverse entity** (per R5 CLAUDE.md §10 / spec §"MUST NOT"). The playbook is
    a data row in the existing `sprk_analysisplaybook` entity. No schema migration. No
    new option-set value. The new action this playbook references is created by task 010;
    co-deploy ordering matters because `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` resolves `actionCode` →
    `sprk_actionid` FK at deploy time.

    **Pure data deploy — no BFF code change**. BFF publish-size delta MUST be exactly
    0 MB (no `dotnet publish` measurement required; confirm in task notes per
    R5 §3.6 / CLAUDE.md §10). No DI changes (ADR-010). No endpoint changes (Auth v2
    inheritance is N/A — this task ships no endpoint).

    **Idempotent deploy**. `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` is idempotent without `-Force` (skips by
    playbook name); a second deploy of the same JSON against Spaarke Dev MUST be a no-op.
    `-Force` is used only when intentionally recreating, and task notes record which mode
    was used.

    R5 is configuration-first. This task is the SECOND of two co-deploying data rows
    that together unblock the entire Phase 2 backend chain (tasks 012 → 014 → 015 →
    017 → 020 → 031). Task 010 ships the action seed; task 011 (this one) ships the
    playbook configuration that wires the action into a runnable orchestration.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior platform engineer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke JPS playbook system
    (`sprk_analysisplaybook` + `sprk_playbooknode` Dataverse entities), the
    `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` deploy script (`actionCode` → FK resolution, dry-run
    semantics, idempotency contract), and the in-repo `*.playbook.json` JSON shape.
    Familiar with `AiAnalysisNodeExecutor` (action_type=0, the standard summarize
    executor) and the platform reuse mandate captured in R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 + §10.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new `sprk_analysisplaybook` row named `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` is
    provisioned on Spaarke Dev and is linked to the `sprk_analysisaction` seed shipped
    by task 010. The playbook definition is committed to the repo at
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Playbooks/summarize-document-for-chat.playbook.json`
    (mirroring the in-repo Insights playbook placement convention). The deploy via
    `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` is idempotent — re-running it against an environment
    that already has the playbook is a no-op without `-Force`. The playbook row carries
    `isSystemPlaybook=true`, `sprk_playbooktype=0` (AiAnalysis), a single `AiAnalysis`
    node referencing the task-010 action via `actionCode`, and a `sprk_configjson` that
    documents `mode=chat-summarize` + cache TTL semantics. Acceptance criteria below
    are all green; quality gates (`code-review` + `adr-check`) pass at Step 9.5; task
    notes record the deploy mode (live vs `-Force`), the resolved playbook GUID on
    Spaarke Dev, and confirm BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </goal>

