  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE.md §3.1)">MUST mirror the in-repo `*.playbook.json` schema (top-level `playbook` block + `nodes[]` + `dependsOnGraph` + `acceptanceCriteria`). MUST NOT invent new schema fields. MUST cite the canonical reference (`predict-matter-cost.playbook.json` + `universal-ingest.playbook.json`) in the playbook's `$comment` header.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 reuse mandate (CLAUDE.md §3.1) — specifically prohibited">MUST NOT introduce a parallel playbook orchestration layer; MUST NOT introduce a new Dataverse entity for playbook configuration; MUST NOT introduce a new prompt-bearing entity (`sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt` IS the JPS primitive; the action seed in task 010 carries it).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §10 (BFF publish-size discipline)">Pure data deploy — no BFF binary impact. Publish-size delta = 0 MB. Confirm explicitly in task notes; no `dotnet publish` measurement required for this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline)">No new feature flag introduced by this task. Kill-switch coverage inherits from existing `Analysis:Enabled` flag via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 (ADR-010 DI minimalism)">N/A — no DI changes. Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec MUST NOT — "MUST NOT introduce new prompt-bearing Dataverse entity"">Reaffirmed. Playbook references task-010 action via `actionCode`; the action row carries `sprk_systemprompt`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-01 acceptance">Playbook output schema lineage matches `ISummarizeResult` from existing wizard path. Encoded in the playbook's `acceptanceCriteria` block as a documentation contract; runtime schema validation is owned by the orchestrator (task 012) + the action's `sprk_systemprompt` JPS schema (task 010).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Co-deploy ordering — `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` resolves `actionCode` → `sprk_actionid` FK at deploy time. Task 010 (action seed) MUST be deployed before task 011 (this task). If running both in the same wave (P2-G1), task 010 deploys first; task 011 deploys second. Document the ordering in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Idempotent deploy — `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` without `-Force` is a no-op when the playbook exists. Verified by running the deploy a second time and confirming the "skipping existing playbook" message. Task notes record the second-run output.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Playbook name MUST follow the `<verb-noun>@v<version>` convention (e.g., `summarize-document-for-chat@v1`) consistent with `universal-ingest@v1`, `predict-matter-cost@v1`. Versioning enables additive evolution without breaking active orchestrators (R6 may ship `@v2`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`isSystemPlaybook=true` per existing system-playbook convention (matches `universal-ingest@v1` + `predict-matter-cost@v1` precedent — system-owned, not user-authored).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>dataverse/playbook-config-deploy</topic>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/universal-ingest.playbook.json</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="In-repo `*.playbook.json` schema (canonical)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Playbooks/predict-matter-cost.playbook.json">
        Use this file as the schema reference. Top-level structure: `$comment` header
        documenting origin + publication + deviations; `playbook` block (name,
        description, isPublic, isSystemPlaybook, sprk_playbooktype, sprk_configjson with
        mode/tier/cacheTtlSeconds/parameterSchema, scopes); `nodes[]` array (each node:
        name, nodeType, actionCode, actionType, outputVariable, positionX/Y, dependsOn,
        configJson); `dependsOnGraph` documentation block; `acceptanceCriteria` block.
        For "Summarize Document for Chat", the playbook will be SINGLE-NODE
        (one AiAnalysis node referencing the task-010 action via actionCode) — much
        simpler than universal-ingest (6 nodes) or predict-matter-cost (8 nodes).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="actionCode FK resolution (Deploy-Playbook.ps1)" location="scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1">
        The deploy script resolves `actionCode` (e.g., `"SUM-CHAT@v1"`) to
        `sprk_actionid` FK at deploy time. This means task 010 (action seed) MUST land in
        Dataverse before task 011 (this playbook) resolves. The script errors with a
        clear "scope record not found" message if the action is missing. Co-deploy
        ordering for P2-G1 is therefore: 010 first, 011 second. If 010 already shipped
        in a prior wave, 011 can run independently.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Single-node AiAnalysis playbook shape" location="docs/architecture/playbook-architecture.md">
        For a single-node AiAnalysis playbook, the node carries:
        `nodeType: "AIAnalysis"`, `actionType: 0` (AiAnalysis enum value),
        `actionCode: "SUM-CHAT@v1"` (or whatever code task 010 uses — confirm at deploy
        time), `outputVariable: "summary"`, and a minimal `configJson` mapping
        playbook parameters (e.g., `fileIds`, `style`) to the action's prompt template.
        The system prompt lives on `sprk_analysisaction.sprk_systemprompt` (task 010);
        this playbook references it via the FK.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Idempotency contract (Deploy-Playbook.ps1)" location="scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1">
        Without `-Force`, the script skips playbooks that already exist by name (printed
        as "Playbook 'X' already exists — skipping"). With `-Force`, it deletes and
        recreates. The second-run verification step below uses no-`-Force` mode to
        confirm idempotency without data destruction.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 010 (D2-01) ships a new `sprk_analysisaction` seed row "Summarize Document for
      Chat" carrying the JPS-formatted system prompt + output schema tuned for
      streaming-aware Summarize output. Task 011 (this task) ships the playbook
      configuration that BINDS that action into a runnable orchestration shape — a row in
      the existing `sprk_analysisplaybook` Dataverse entity, deployed via the existing
      `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` script. Together, tasks 010 + 011 are the
      "configuration half" of the chat-driven Summarize vertical slice; the
      orchestrator (task 012), endpoint (task 014), and agent tool (task 015) are the
      "code half" that consumes this configuration.

      The existing Summarize playbook (GUID `4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988`) is
      the wizard-path playbook referenced by `SummarizeFilesDialog` /
      `summarizeService.ts` in LegalWorkspace. It stays unchanged. The new
      "Summarize Document for Chat" playbook is its chat-pane sibling — sharing the
      output schema family (`ISummarizeResult` / `DocumentAnalysisResult`) but tuned for
      streaming-aware execution via the Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs mode landed in
      task 006 (D1-06), with progressive `FieldDelta` SSE emission landed in task 005
      (D1-05). Per design.md §2: "R5 is not a re-implementation of summary functionality.
      The Summarize playbook ... and its endpoint already exist; R5 re-surfaces them
      through the chat pane and adds session-scoped grounding for follow-up turns."
      Task 011 is the configuration row that operationalises that re-surfacing.

      Reuse-mandate framing (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1): R5 ships zero new ADRs, zero new
      Dataverse entities, zero new orchestrators, zero new chat agents. New AI
      capabilities arrive via NEW DATA ROWS in EXISTING entities (`sprk_analysisaction`
      + `sprk_analysisplaybook`) plus thin orchestration. Tasks 010 + 011 are the
      first operator-visible proof of that pattern in R5.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="010" status="not-started">
        Action seed "Summarize Document for Chat" must be deployed to Spaarke Dev first.
        `Deploy-Playbook.ps1` resolves `actionCode` → `sprk_actionid` FK at deploy time;
        missing action = deploy error. Co-deploy ordering within P2-G1: 010 → 011.
      </dependency>
      <dependency task="Phase 1 ✅" status="complete">
        All Phase 1 tasks (001–009) must be complete: session-files index provisioned;
        `RagSearchOptions.sessionId` extended; `RagIndexingPipeline` parameterised;
        `ChatSession.UploadedFiles` extended; `AnalysisChunk.FieldDelta` variant landed;
        Azure OpenAI Structured Outputs + incremental JSON parser shipped; cleanup
        `IHostedService` running; telemetry events emitting; tests + publish-size verified.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Existing Summarize playbook (GUID `4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988`) —
        wizard-path Summarize; reused unchanged per design.md §2 / coordination doc §3.2.
        This new playbook is its chat-pane sibling, not a replacement.</item>
      <item>`universal-ingest@v1` (Insights r2 Wave C task 020) +
        `predict-matter-cost@v1` (Insights r1) — the two canonical in-repo
        `*.playbook.json` definitions. Task 011 mirrors their schema shape exactly.</item>
      <item>Task 010 (D2-01) — co-deploying action seed. Their POML files reference
        each other; their commits land together; their notes reference each other for
        deploy ordering evidence.</item>
      <item>Task 012 (D2-03 `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`) — depends on this playbook
        existing in Dataverse. Resolves the playbook by name (`summarize-document-for-chat@v1`)
        at request time.</item>
      <item>Task 014 (D2-04 `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` endpoint) +
        task 015 (D2-05 `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` agent tool) — both downstream
