      <item>R6+ — additional playbooks (`/analyze`, `/compare`, `/translate`, `/extract`)
        will follow the same `sprk_analysisaction` + `sprk_analysisplaybook` co-deploy
        pattern; Phase 3 D3-01 (task 040) validates this via `/analyze` proof point.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`.
      Declare RIGOR LEVEL per CLAUDE.md §8:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Dataverse data deploy with downstream-blocker semantics
         (gates tasks 012 / 014 / 015 / 017 / 020 / 031); tag set includes
         `dataverse` + `playbook` + `data-deploy` (FULL-rigor per CLAUDE.md §8
         decision tree); R5 CLAUDE.md mandates FULL for all R5 tasks
         (§4 "R5 rigor level: FULL for all tasks").
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: All Step 0–10 of this POML; quality gates at Step 9.5.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`. Confirm task 011 status is 🔲, parallel-safe = true,
      wave = P2-G1, dependencies = "Phase 1 ✅". Confirm task 010 status (the co-deploy
      partner) — if 🔲 and queued in the same wave, coordinate to ensure 010 deploys
      first; if ✅, this task can proceed independently. Read `current-task.md` to verify
      no prior R5 task is in flight that would conflict. Confirm Phase 1 is fully
      complete (all P1-G1 through P1-G5 tasks ✅).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract
      from `predict-matter-cost.playbook.json` and `universal-ingest.playbook.json`: the
      exact JSON schema shape (top-level keys, the `playbook` block structure, the
      `nodes[]` element shape with `actionCode` + `actionType` + `outputVariable` +
      `configJson`, the `dependsOnGraph` block, the `acceptanceCriteria` block). Read
      `scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` parameter documentation + the `actionCode` →
      `sprk_actionid` resolution path to confirm the deploy semantics this task relies
      on. Read task 010's POML to confirm the exact `actionCode` value the task ships
      (the playbook will reference it verbatim; record it in task notes).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Confirm task-010 action seed details">
      Open the task 010 POML and locate: (a) the action's `actionCode` value (likely
      something like `"SUM-CHAT@v1"` — confirm; this task's playbook references it
      verbatim); (b) the action's `sprk_executoractiontype` value (expected: `0` for
      AiAnalysis); (c) the action's `outputVariable` semantics (expected: produces a
      `summary` output matching the `ISummarizeResult` / `DocumentAnalysisResult` shape
      per FR-01 acceptance). Record these values in task notes — the playbook node
      configJson uses them. If task 010 has not yet shipped (P2-G1 co-wave), coordinate
      with the operator: 010 must land first OR both deploy together with 010 ordered
      first in the deploy script invocation sequence.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author the playbook JSON">
      Create
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Playbooks/summarize-document-for-chat.playbook.json`
      (NEW directory + NEW file; mirrors the in-repo Insights `Playbooks/` placement
      convention). Schema (copy shape verbatim from
      `predict-matter-cost.playbook.json` then specialise):

      ```json
      {
        "$comment": "Spaarke AI Platform Unification R5 (task 011 / D2-02) — Chat-driven Summarize-for-Chat playbook configuration. Single-node AiAnalysis playbook binding the task-010 action seed ('Summarize Document for Chat', actionCode 'SUM-CHAT@v1') into a runnable orchestration. Mirrors the schema shape of universal-ingest.playbook.json + predict-matter-cost.playbook.json (the canonical in-repo *.playbook.json references). The wizard-path Summarize playbook (GUID 4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988) stays unchanged; this is its chat-pane sibling per R5 design.md §2. Deploy via: scripts/Deploy-Playbook.ps1 -DefinitionFile <this-file> after az login. Idempotent without -Force.",
        "$comment-publication": "Published as a Dataverse sprk_analysisplaybook row + 1 sprk_playbooknodes row. The SessionSummarizeOrchestrator (R5 task 012 / D2-03) resolves this playbook by name and invokes it from both the direct endpoint POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize (task 014 / D2-04) and the InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool agent-tool path (task 015 / D2-05). Together they form the chat-driven Summarize vertical slice (FR-01 / FR-02).",

        "playbook": {
          "name": "summarize-document-for-chat@v1",
          "description": "Chat-driven Summarize-for-Chat playbook (R5 D2-02). Single AiAnalysis node executes the SUM-CHAT@v1 action against 1–N session-scoped files; emits structured ISummarizeResult-shaped output (TL;DR, summary, fileHighlights[], mentioned parties, call-to-action) with progressive FieldDelta SSE emission per task 006 (D1-06) Structured Outputs + incremental JSON parser. Output schema family matches the existing wizard-path Summarize playbook (GUID 4a72f99c-a119-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988); this is its chat-pane sibling.",
          "isPublic": false,
          "isSystemPlaybook": true,
          "sprk_playbooktype": 0,
          "$comment-type": "sprk_playbooktype=0 (AiAnalysis) — matches universal-ingest@v1 + predict-matter-cost@v1 convention. System-owned (isSystemPlaybook=true), not user-authored.",
          "sprk_configjson": {
            "mode": "chat-summarize",
            "tier": "inference",
            "cacheTtlSeconds": 0,
            "$comment-cacheTtl": "Cache TTL = 0 — Summarize-for-Chat is per-session and per-file-set; the file set changes mid-session as users upload/remove files (per FR-08 + R5 §3.8 20-file cap). Idempotency comes from session-files index isolation (task 001) + per-invocation file-set targeting, not from cache.",
            "parameterSchema": {
              "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
              "type": "object",
              "required": ["sessionId", "tenantId"],
              "properties": {
                "sessionId": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "description": "Chat session GUID. Used by RagService.SearchAsync(sessionId=...) per task 002 to scope retrieval to the spaarke-session-files index slice for this session. Required for tenant + session isolation per ADR-014."
                },
                "tenantId": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "description": "Tenant ID for multi-tenant isolation per ADR-014. Required on every spaarke-session-files index query."
                },
                "fileIds": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": { "type": "string" },
                  "description": "OPTIONAL — subset of session-uploaded files to summarize (e.g., from FR-08 'summarize just one of the files'). When absent, all files in ChatSession.UploadedFiles per task 004 are summarized as a combined-summary (FR-04 multi-file acknowledgement)."
                },
                "style": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "description": "OPTIONAL — natural-language style hint passed through to the action's system prompt (e.g., 'executive', 'detailed', 'bullet-points'). Action interprets via the JPS prompt template authored in task 010."
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "scopes": {
            "actions": [],
            "skills": [],
            "knowledge": [],
            "tools": []
          },
          "$comment-scopes": "Scopes left empty intentionally — matches universal-ingest@v1 + predict-matter-cost@v1 convention. The single node's executor (AiAnalysisNodeExecutor for actionType=0) is auto-discovered by NodeExecutorRegistry; per-node scope binding via actionCode FK is sufficient."
        },

        "nodes": [
          {
            "name": "summarize",
            "nodeType": "AIAnalysis",
            "actionCode": "SUM-CHAT@v1",
            "$comment-actionCode": "R5 task 010 (D2-01) ships sprk_analysisaction row with this actionCode. Deploy-Playbook.ps1 resolves to sprk_actionid FK at deploy time; missing action = deploy error. Verify the actionCode value matches task 010's authored value before deploying this playbook.",
            "actionType": 0,
            "$comment-actionType": "ActionType.AiAnalysis = 0; handled by AiAnalysisNodeExecutor (existing platform executor — no new node executor needed per R5 reuse mandate). The task-010 action carries sprk_systemprompt with the JPS-formatted Summarize-for-Chat prompt + output schema.",
            "outputVariable": "summary",
            "positionX": 400, "positionY": 200,
            "configJson": {
              "sessionIdFrom": "parameters.sessionId",
              "tenantIdFrom": "parameters.tenantId",
              "fileIdsFrom": "parameters.fileIds",
              "styleFrom": "parameters.style",
              "$comment": "AiAnalysisNodeExecutor receives session + tenant + file scope via parameters. The actual document text retrieval is performed by the orchestrator (R5 task 012) via the session-files index slice (task 001) before invoking this playbook. The Structured Outputs mode + incremental JSON parser (task 006 / D1-06) emit progressive FieldDelta SSE events as the model streams; the StructuredOutputStreamWidget (task 017 / D2-07) renders the deltas in the Workspace pane."
            }
          }
        ],

        "dependsOnGraph": {
          "$comment": "Single-node playbook — no edges. Mirrors the structural shape of multi-node playbooks for tooling consistency.",
          "edges": []
        },

        "acceptanceCriteria": {
          "$comment": "Mirrors task 011 POML <acceptance-criteria>. Used as documentation + smoke-test fixture targets for the orchestrator (task 012) + endpoint (task 014) integration tests.",
          "criteria": [
            "Playbook publishes successfully (sprk_analysisplaybook row + 1 sprk_playbooknodes row in Dataverse, name='summarize-document-for-chat@v1', isSystemPlaybook=true)",
            "Lint check passes — the single node has actionCode reference 'SUM-CHAT@v1' resolving to the task-010 action row",
            "Output schema family matches the existing wizard-path Summarize playbook (ISummarizeResult / DocumentAnalysisResult per spec FR-01)",
            "Re-running Deploy-Playbook.ps1 without -Force is idempotent (no-op; 'skipping existing playbook' message)"
          ]
        }
      }
      ```

      Diff against `predict-matter-cost.playbook.json` to verify only intentional shape
      deviations (single-node vs 8-node; `mode: chat-summarize` vs `mode: insights`;
      `cacheTtlSeconds: 0` vs `300`; `isPublic: false`; parameterSchema specialised).
